      <p>A <a href="ch64s03.html#MonstersDr-Dw201">dragonne</a> possesses huge claws and fangs, and large eyes, usually the color of its scales. A <a href="ch64s03.html#MonstersDr-Dw201">dragonne</a> is about 12 feet long and weighs about 700 pounds.<a href="img/MonstersDr-Dw.Dragonne.jpg" target="_blank"><span class="inlinemediaobject"><img src="thumb/MonstersDr-Dw.Dragonne.jpg" align="right"/></span></a></p>
      <p><a href="ch64s03.html#MonstersDr-Dw201">Dragonnes</a> speak Draconic.</p>
      <div class="sect4" lang="en">
        <div class="titlepage">
          <div>
            <div>
              <h5 class="title"><a name="id1957113"/>Combat</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
          <div class="keyword">monsterinfo</div>
        </div>
        <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersDr-Dw202"/>
        <p>A <a href="ch64s03.html#MonstersDr-Dw201">dragonne's</a> wings are useful only for short flights, carrying the creature for 10 to 30 minutes at a time. Nevertheless, it uses its wings effectively in battle. If opponents attempt to charge or encircle it, the <a href="ch64s03.html#MonstersDr-Dw201">dragonne</a> simply takes to the air and finds a more defensible position.</p>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id1957158"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersDr-Dw203"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Pounce (Ex):</strong></span> If a <a href="ch64s03.html#MonstersDr-Dw201">dragonne</a> charges, it can make a full attack in the same round.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id1957197"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersDr-Dw204"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Roar (Su):</strong></span> A <a href="ch64s03.html#MonstersDr-Dw201">dragonne</a> can loose a devastating roar every 1d4 rounds. All creatures except <a href="ch64s03.html#MonstersDr-Dw201">dragonnes</a> within 120 feet must succeed on a DC 15 Will save or become fatigued. Those within 30 feet who fail their saves become exhausted. The save DC is Charisma-based.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id1957248"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersDr-Dw205"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Skills:</strong></span> <a href="ch64s03.html#MonstersDr-Dw201">Dragonnes</a> have a +4 racial bonus on <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills204">Listen</a> and <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills294">Spot</a> checks.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id1957306"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersDr-Dw206"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Carrying Capacity:</strong></span> A light load for a <a href="ch64s03.html#MonstersDr-Dw201">dragonne</a> is up to 348 pounds; a medium load, 349-699 pounds, and a heavy load, 700-1,050 pounds.</p>
